  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nThere is a just a few lines that actually explain \"how\" to implement Narayana transactions on reactive APIs.\r\n\r\nReactive Narayana doc: https://quarkus.io/guides/transaction#reactive-extensions\r\n\r\nLooks that the only way to implement transactions on a Reactive API is using the declarative approach (\"`@Transaction` annotation\"), but is not 100% clear to me. \r\n\r\nAlso, I could not find any example that covers the following extension:\r\n\r\n```\r\nquarkus-narayana-jta\r\nquarkus-hibernate-reactive-panache\r\nquarkus-resteasy-reactive\r\nquarkus-reactive-pg-client\r\n```\r\n\r\nWould be great to have at least some snippets that show you how to set up a reactive API with Narayana (or a quickstart example)\r\n\r\n",
